fields.name: Philodendron Hastatum Silver Sword
fields.description: Extremely hard for us to keep a constant stock of these philodendron they are a must have in any plant collection. The colour of the leaves gives it a real modern feel and will make it a fantastic talking point in your home. Easy to propagate they are a quick growing climber complete with it's own trellis.

fields.name: Calathea Makoyana
fields.description: It's no wonder calathea's are such a popular houseplant, with their large variety of beautiful markings, each variety different to the last they add a gorgeous vibrancy to your home! Calathea Makoyana's is nicknamed peacock plant, the leaves markings are similar to that of a peacock tail!

fields.name: Ficus Elastica Tineke
fields.description: A beautiful variegated variety of the traditional rubber plant would make a lovely addition to your collection! The big glossy leaves with shades of green and cream make this guy a real eye-catcher!

fields.name: Stromanthe Triostar
fields.description: A close relation to calathea, Stromanthe Triostar is one of the brightest bold houseplants out there. Each leaf is slightly different with the cream, green purple and pink variegation working wonderfully with the bright purple/pink underside.

fields.name: Peperomia Argyreia 'Watermelon'
fields.description: Like their namesake the leaves of the Peperomia Argyreia have lovely green and silver stripes, like the flesh of a watermelon. A real stand out to your collection, that are very easy to grow, would make a great choice for a beginner!

fields.name: Calathea Ornata
fields.description: It's no wonder calathea's are such a popular houseplant, with their large variety of beautiful markings, each variety different to the last they add a gorgeous vibrancy to your home! Calathea Ornata's leaves have deep green veins on a white background, flushed with a soft pink. The underside of the leaves also has a darker pink colouring. As the leaves are quite firm and stand away from the plant this helps to show off the wonderful pattern and colouring on each leaf.

fields.name: Monstera Deliciosa
fields.description: More commonly known as Swiss cheese plant. This easy to care for plant is a great way to add some greenery into your space.

fields.name: Philodendron Birkin
fields.description: We are very pleased to have been able to get our hands on some extremely rare Philodrendron Birkins! Beautiful striped leaves make this guy a real eye catcher! One for your collection!

fields.name: Alocasia zebrina 'Tiger'
fields.description: The Alocasia Zebrina is a beautiful tropical plant. Its large leaves really stand out, but also its zebra-like stems are beautiful. It's not the easiest plant to take care of though and it will drop some leaves, but this is nothing to worry about. If you take good care of this plant, it'll only drop its old leaves to make space for large new leaves.

fields.name: Zamioculcas zamiifolia 'Raven'
fields.description: Like many indoor plants, Zamioculas can improve the quality of air in an indoor space. But unlike others, he can also improve human health in these spaces, as it's recently been found that he can remove carcinogens, such as Benzene, that are often found in a home.

fields.name: Calathea Lancifolia Rattlesnake
fields.description: It's no wonder calathea's are such a popular houseplant, with their large variety of beautiful markings, each variety different to the last they add a gorgeous vibrancy to your home! Calathea Lancifolia is a wonderfully showy houseplant. It has upright, lance-shaped leaves with long wavy edges that form in clumps, spreading slowly over time. The leaves are variegated with dark green strokes on a pale green background. The undersides are a burgundy red and velvety to the touch.

fields.name: Rhaphidophora Tetrasperma
fields.description: The Rhaphidophora Tetrasperma is also often referred to as Mini Monstera, although not in the same family the leaves are similar. It has an interesting leaf shape, though much smaller than your usual Monstera Deliciosa.

fields.name: Senecio rowleyanus
fields.description: Senecio rowleyanus aka \"String of Beads\", is a succulent with trailing stems and round bead-like leaves. This creeping, perennial, succulent vine is native to the drier parts of southwest Africa, making it uniquely drought-proof and suitable for beginner house plant owners. It is well suited to a hanging basket or a high bookshelf, to allow its long foliage to hang down.

fields.name: Asparagus Fern
fields.description: Native to Africa, Asparagus Fern is an elegant plant, with slender stems and near horizontal spreading frond-like branches. Initially bushy, the stems become more tendril-like as the plant matures. They are having a resurgence in popularity as a houseplant they have lovely delicate lace like foliage.

fields.name: Ficus elastica 'Abidjan'
fields.description: Ficus elastica are part of the Moraceae family, 'Ficus' being the Latin for 'Fig'.They are native to the Himalayas, Malaysia, Sumatra and Java. Ficus elastica are often called 'Rubber Plants' and they have large, shiny, leathery leaves with obvious midribs. Each leaf emerges from a bright red protective sheath.

fields.name: Epipremnum aureum - Devils Ivy, Pothos
fields.description: This vining plant is part of the Araceae family and is native to the Solomon Islands where they climb high up the trunks and along branches of trees by attaching their fleshy aerial roots to bark. Epipremnum have leathery leaves which are almost heart shaped.

fields.name: Ficus elastica 'Belize'
fields.description: This pink variation on the classic rubber tree - is a perfect addition to your plant collection.

fields.name: Euphorbia Variegated
fields.description: Variegated Euphorbia! Native to Yemen and Saudi Arabia this cactus has a sturdy trunk and is multi-branched and edged with short sharp spines. The variegation gives this guy a gorgeous white skinned appearance. A real fast grower you'll be shocked at how tall he'll get!

fields.name: Peperomia Prostrata 'String of Turtles'
fields.description: Peperomia Prostrata is the must have plant for your collection. Its leaves are round and fleshy and are variegated in such a way that they look like turtle shells!

fields.name: Ceropegia woodii 'Marlies Variegata'
fields.description: String of Hearts also known as Rosary Vine, is a trailing semi-succulent, native to S. Africa. This beautiful variegated plant has splashed of white and pink.

fields.name: Calathea 'White Star'
fields.description: Native to the subtropics, particularly the rainforests of Brazil, this stunning decorative plant has gorgeous large dark green with striking white stripes. This plant is a type of Calathea so you will notice that the leaves open and close from day to night. This plant is also a great for air purifying.

fields.name: Calathea Orbifolia
fields.description: Calathea orbifolia is part of the Marantaceae family and is native to Bolivia. It has large rounded leaves with silver and green stripes. They can grow up to a metre in height and leaves 30cm across.
